The paper deals with pricing strategies for revenue maximization, which is a topic in algorithmic game theory (cs.GT) and computational economics (cs.EC). The problem involves designing algorithms to allocate limited resources (limited supply setting), which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the use of subadditive valuation functions, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information theory (cs.IT).
